{
  "argument_loc": "Unspecified",
  "description": "[[File:matrixMultiply.jpg|right|600px]]\nReturns resulting matrix from the {{Link|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrix_multiplication|multiplication}} of two matrices. First matrix must be of the size n &times; '''k''', while the second must be of the size '''k''' &times; m, i.e {{hl|columns}} matrix1 == {{hl|rows}} matrix2. The resulting matrix will be of the size n &times; m. If the shapes do not match, empty array [] will be returned.",
  "effect_loc": "Unspecified",
  "examples": [
    "<sqf>\n[\n\t[2],\n\t[2]\n] \nmatrixMultiply \n[\n\t[3] \n]\n/* returns \n[\n\t[6],\n\t[6]\n] */\n</sqf>",
    "<sqf>\n[\n\t[-1,0,0],\n\t[0,-1,0]\n] \nmatrixMultiply \n[\n\t[1,2],\n\t[3,1],\n\t[2,3]\n] \n/* returns \n[\n\t[-1,-2],\n\t[-3,-1]\n] */\n</sqf>"
  ],
